SIMPLE: darwinian
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Darwinian
<hw>Dar*win"i*an</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[From the name of
Charles <ets>Darwin</ets>, an English scientist.]</ety> <def>Pertaining
to Darwin; <as>as, the <ex>Darwinian</ex> theory, a theory of the manner
and cause of the supposed development of living things from certain
original forms or elements</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ This theory was put forth by Darwin in 1859 in a work
entitled ⟦ldquo⟧The Origin of species by Means of Natural
Selection.⟦rdquo⟧ The author argues that, in the struggle for existence,
those plants and creatures best fitted to the requirements of the
situation in which they are placed are the ones that will live; in other
words, that Nature selects those which are to survive. This is the
theory of <xex>natural selection</xex> or the <xex>survival of the
fittest</xex>. He also argues that natural selection is capable of
modifying and producing organisms fit for their circumstances. See
<cref>Development theory</cref>, under <er>Development</er>.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Darwinian</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Darwinian
<hw>Dar*win"i*an</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>An advocate of
Darwinism.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Darwinianism</ent>⟦br⟧
